3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper presents a new method of specification and verification of security protocols, which may involve programming languages and their semantics.
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The verification of security protocols is an important aspect of software engineering, and the paper may provide insights into the development of secure software systems.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The process model of security protocols may involve the use of data structures and algorithms, which makes cs.DS a possible sub-category.
